1
00:00:07,950 --> 00:00:09,190
What are you so attached to?

2
00:00:09,220 --> 00:00:11,770
The person from your dreams is just
a fancy phrase that can't pay the bills.

3
00:00:11,790 --> 00:00:13,400
- Are you Khun Jarinda?
- Yes.

4
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:15,280
- Could you sign for this, please?
- Hey! Hold on!

5
00:00:15,310 --> 00:00:17,590
I’m going to find a way to send you back.

6
00:00:17,790 --> 00:00:22,020
Greetings. I am Robot Model A382.

7
00:00:22,040 --> 00:00:24,330
My duty is to ensure user satisfaction.

8
00:00:27,330 --> 00:00:29,810
Do you prefer rabbits or cats, Master?

9
00:00:30,090 --> 00:00:31,200
Meow.

10
00:00:31,220 --> 00:00:33,710
THAT IS ENOUGH!!!!

11
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:34,890
What are you up to again?

12
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:36,960
I’m analyzing this bracelet.

13
00:00:36,990 --> 00:00:37,810
Give it back!

14
00:00:39,320 --> 00:00:39,920
Ai.

15
00:00:41,670 --> 00:00:42,360
AI.

16
00:00:45,690 --> 00:00:47,070
Oh shit!

17
00:00:50,150 --> 00:00:50,880
Ai!

18
00:00:52,500 --> 00:00:53,190
Ai!

19
00:00:53,770 --> 00:00:56,410
Where are you? This isn't funny!

20
00:01:02,420 --> 00:01:04,660
Where could a robot that's
only a few days old have gone?

21
00:01:13,820 --> 00:01:14,610
Whatever.

22
00:01:15,680 --> 00:01:16,670
Good riddance.

23
00:01:39,990 --> 00:01:41,330
I’m going crazy!

24
00:01:43,190 --> 00:01:43,990
Ai!

25
00:01:45,500 --> 00:01:46,270
Ai!

26
00:01:48,120 --> 00:01:48,840
Ai!

27
00:01:56,270 --> 00:01:58,680
So who are you?
How come I’ve never seen you before?

28
00:02:03,270 --> 00:02:04,080
Ai Josh.

29
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:08,190
I saw you running out of P’ Gen’s house.
What's your relationship with her?

30
00:02:08,370 --> 00:02:11,060
P’ Gen has lived here for three years.

31
00:02:11,410 --> 00:02:13,390
I’ve never seen her bring a single friend home.

32
00:02:13,420 --> 00:02:16,570
Someone as beautiful as you shouldn't
be friends with someone like her.

33
00:02:16,590 --> 00:02:20,710
It’s not just friends.
Gen never brings anyone home at all.

34
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:23,690
So people started saying she has no friends.

35
00:02:26,460 --> 00:02:30,190
You’re right, honey. No matter how
heavenly beautiful this young lady is,

36
00:02:30,220 --> 00:02:32,120
she still can't compete with you.

37
00:02:32,410 --> 00:02:34,590
Gosh! Who's talking about looks?

38
00:02:34,630 --> 00:02:38,910
And close your mouth. You're
drooling all the way down to the floor.

39
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:41,090
- Ouch! Ouch!
- Stop. Stop!

40
00:02:43,490 --> 00:02:44,790
So who exactly are you?

41
00:02:45,520 --> 00:02:46,730
And what’s your background?

42
00:02:46,750 --> 00:02:51,390
How did you end up living with that
foul-mouthed brat—uh, I mean, Gen?

43
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:54,990
Auntie, try saying that to P’ Gen's face.

44
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:57,980
She'll pluck every last gray hair off your head.

45
00:02:58,480 --> 00:03:01,320
My name is Ai.
Master gave me this name.

46
00:03:02,640 --> 00:03:06,190
What Master? Are you guys
doing some roleplay? Ohhh?

47
00:03:06,210 --> 00:03:07,970
Come to think of it,
with a face like that,

48
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:11,880
if you wore a maid outfit
and went “Yes, master~,” …

49
00:03:12,740 --> 00:03:13,930
Stop messing around!

50
00:03:13,950 --> 00:03:15,920
Your mind always goes straight to the gutter.

51
00:03:15,940 --> 00:03:17,060
I’ve worn one before.

52
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:19,829
For my Master.

53
00:03:20,540 --> 00:03:23,079
But it looks like she didn’t like it,

54
00:03:24,470 --> 00:03:26,130
so I switched to a bunny outfit instead.

55
00:03:35,450 --> 00:03:41,760
Do any of you know what I
need to do to repair this bracelet?

56
00:03:47,610 --> 00:03:49,530
Uh… well…

57
00:03:50,990 --> 00:03:53,960
The string’s totally worn out.
It can’t be fixed, dear.

58
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:59,720
When something is broken, just let it be.

59
00:04:00,190 --> 00:04:04,670
Even when a customer breaks
my plate, I still have to accept it.

60
00:04:06,010 --> 00:04:07,680
Give me a break, Auntie.

61
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:13,050
A customer dropped a spoon the other
day and you chased them out with a broom.

62
00:04:14,030 --> 00:04:16,269
Trying to get her in as
a new customer, aren’t you?

63
00:04:16,610 --> 00:04:18,700
Don’t think you can fool me.

64
00:04:24,630 --> 00:04:26,020
Do you really not mind it?

65
00:04:32,600 --> 00:04:33,470
Really?

66
00:04:33,920 --> 00:04:35,280
Wait, wait, wait, wait, wait—!

67
00:04:36,050 --> 00:04:36,850
Ai!

68
00:04:37,220 --> 00:04:38,350
Master!

69
00:04:41,580 --> 00:04:42,550
Come with me.

70
00:04:48,460 --> 00:04:50,940
I’ll pay you back for it later, Auntie.
Let’s go.

71
00:04:50,960 --> 00:04:52,940
- Hold on!
- Come on, Auntie.

72
00:04:53,310 --> 00:04:54,720
Don't take it out on a kid.

73
00:04:54,820 --> 00:04:57,400
A kid? You’re calling
a grown-ass woman a kid?!

74
00:04:57,860 --> 00:04:58,890
Calm down, Auntie.

75
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:02,130
At your age, you don’t
want to get a heart attack.

76
00:05:02,710 --> 00:05:04,500
Ai, Run! Quick!

77
00:05:04,630 --> 00:05:05,830
Ai Gen!

78
00:05:06,630 --> 00:05:07,410
Ai Gen!

79
00:05:08,040 --> 00:05:09,380
Thought you didn’t mind, Auntie.

80
00:05:10,670 --> 00:05:13,680
You damn brat!
You and your filthy little mouth!

81
00:07:18,890 --> 00:07:20,670
Alright, we need to talk.

82
00:07:21,070 --> 00:07:22,890
I’m always ready to talk with Master.

83
00:07:22,920 --> 00:07:26,260
But statistically, out of ten times
I try to start a conversation with you,

84
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:28,590
only about one or two times do you actually—

85
00:07:28,620 --> 00:07:32,010
Enough. Stop that robot
statistical nonsense of yours.

86
00:07:32,310 --> 00:07:34,360
Can I buy you out of saying things like

87
00:07:34,390 --> 00:07:38,370
"Statistically speaking," "Based on my
scan," "According to the data I found"?

88
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,240
Are you trying to let the whole
world know you're a robot?

89
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:43,480
No, I can't publicly disclose that.

90
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:47,200
My system prohibits me from revealing
that I'm a robot to anyone other than you.

91
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,310
It’s company policy.

92
00:08:02,080 --> 00:08:04,820
Where are you going, Master?
Don’t you want to talk to me?

93
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:08,760
I— I am talking to you.

94
00:08:08,880 --> 00:08:10,730
It’s just that you’re too close.

95
00:08:11,650 --> 00:08:14,540
It’s not too close.
I can even sit on your lap, Master.

96
00:08:22,610 --> 00:08:23,480
Is this close enough?

97
00:08:28,930 --> 00:08:32,220
So, why did you go around
breaking other people’s things?

98
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:34,610
Breaking things?

99
00:08:35,240 --> 00:08:37,440
You know, when you were
throwing plates around just now.

100
00:08:38,500 --> 00:08:40,140
I wasn’t breaking things.

101
00:08:40,380 --> 00:08:43,000
The shop owner said
she wouldn’t mind if I did it.

102
00:08:43,350 --> 00:08:46,640
She also said that when something
is broken, just let it be.

103
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:48,560
Like the plate I broke.

104
00:08:50,630 --> 00:08:52,210
Did I do something wrong, Master?

105
00:08:52,840 --> 00:08:56,980
I just wanted to know whether breaking
a plate would make the shop owner angry,

106
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:58,660
like how you got angry with me.

107
00:08:59,490 --> 00:09:00,680
I’m not angry with you.

108
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:01,990
But according to the scan—

109
00:09:04,990 --> 00:09:06,040
I’m angry at myself.

110
00:09:08,870 --> 00:09:10,440
Why are you angry at yourself?

111
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:17,420
Because… I failed to take good
care of something precious to me.

112
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:19,470
And I even took it out on you.

113
00:09:21,670 --> 00:09:22,740
I'm sorry.

114
00:09:44,910 --> 00:09:48,280
You took it out on me, Master?
When? When was it?

115
00:09:51,180 --> 00:09:52,960
You’re just like a three-year-old.

116
00:09:53,770 --> 00:09:55,760
- Not three years old.
- Then two years old.

117
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:56,880
No.

118
00:09:57,240 --> 00:10:01,900
Since activation, I am 4 days,
3 hours, and 15 minutes old.

119
00:10:07,670 --> 00:10:09,030
You’re hurting me, Master.

120
00:10:14,030 --> 00:10:16,570
Since I did something wrong,
guess I have to make up for it.

121
00:10:17,870 --> 00:10:21,720
How about starting by teaching
a four-day-old robot how to be human?

122
00:10:21,900 --> 00:10:23,770
But I can learn from the system.

123
00:10:24,170 --> 00:10:27,130
The most important basic
rule right now—number one:

124
00:10:27,650 --> 00:10:28,890
stop trusting the system!

125
00:10:38,000 --> 00:10:39,770
(Auntie Kai)
This is Auntie Kai, the neighborhood gossip.

126
00:10:39,790 --> 00:10:41,500
Take whatever she says with a grain of salt.

127
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:44,280
She doesn't run her made-to-order
restaurant to make a living.

128
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:45,790
She runs it to spy on the neighbors.

129
00:10:46,050 --> 00:10:48,950
And stop calling her "Shop Owner."
Call her "Auntie."

130
00:10:49,220 --> 00:10:51,320
Repeat after me: Auntie.

131
00:10:52,460 --> 00:10:53,220
Auntie.

132
00:10:56,470 --> 00:10:58,130
Trash

133
00:11:01,010 --> 00:11:04,190
These two are P’ Wanda and P’ Zoon
—the dynamic duo from hell.

134
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:04,170
(Wanda & Zoon)

135
00:11:04,210 --> 00:11:08,010
If you see them, make a run for it.
If you can't, just say,

136
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:11,860
"P’ Wanda, have you done
something? You look prettier!" Then run.

137
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:14,560
The husband isn't the problem.
Just make sure you outrun the wife.

138
00:11:14,580 --> 00:11:15,430
Got it?

139
00:11:37,570 --> 00:11:40,120
The last one, this kid lives around here.

140
00:11:40,010 --> 00:11:41,320
(Josh)

141
00:11:40,410 --> 00:11:41,800
He’s a motorcycle taxi driver.

142
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:45,160
He’s younger than me,
so no need to call him "P’ Josh."

143
00:11:45,190 --> 00:11:46,600
Just "Josh" is enough.

144
00:11:47,910 --> 00:11:49,070
Just Josh?

145
00:11:52,390 --> 00:11:53,650
Are you screwing with me?

146
00:11:54,650 --> 00:11:57,580
I am not.
How does one do that?

147
00:11:58,860 --> 00:12:01,210
The word “screw” is something
I’m not supposed to say,

148
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:04,190
since it’s considered
an impolite word in my database.

149
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:14,650
Look!

150
00:12:16,160 --> 00:12:18,040
You really know nothing at all.

151
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:21,820
Master is criticizing me again.

152
00:12:47,230 --> 00:12:49,170
You’re really just as beautiful as I imagined.

153
00:12:52,450 --> 00:12:53,460
Master...

154
00:12:58,560 --> 00:13:00,320
Do you like my face?

155
00:13:06,360 --> 00:13:07,210
Gen.

156
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:11,610
Just call me Gen.

157
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:16,050
Gen.

158
00:13:38,340 --> 00:13:39,450
Today's lesson is over.

159
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:44,550
I— I'm sleepy.

160
00:13:46,770 --> 00:13:48,370
I’m... going to bed.

161
00:14:33,140 --> 00:14:34,150
What's wrong with you?

162
00:14:46,170 --> 00:14:47,740
Why did you not let me to cook?

163
00:14:48,040 --> 00:14:50,740
I have a database of recipes
from almost every cuisine,

164
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:52,860
and I know all the exact ingredient ratios.

165
00:14:53,660 --> 00:14:55,680
So why do you still cook yourself, Master?

166
00:14:57,210 --> 00:15:00,000
I’m a robot designed to
ensure my master's satisfaction.

167
00:15:00,030 --> 00:15:02,210
Right. Exact ratios.

168
00:15:02,520 --> 00:15:04,630
But last time, the pork was raw,
the rice stuck to the pan,

169
00:15:04,650 --> 00:15:06,920
and you couldn't even tell
if the oil was hot or burning.

170
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:08,940
There's no way I’d trust you to cook.

171
00:15:10,340 --> 00:15:13,530
And when will you stop calling me Master?
I told you to call me Gen.

172
00:15:19,520 --> 00:15:21,500
Do you know that you’re mean, Gen?

173
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:25,720
You're saying I’m mean?
Do you even know what ‘mean’ means?

174
00:15:29,020 --> 00:15:30,100
You have a point.

175
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:33,220
Why do I perceive you as mean,

176
00:15:34,180 --> 00:15:36,330
even though you cooked for me?

177
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:40,960
Well… maybe it’s because

178
00:15:40,990 --> 00:15:43,750
you’ve grown from a 4-day-old
robot into a week-and-a-half-old robot.

179
00:15:46,010 --> 00:15:47,170
Time to eat.

180
00:16:00,060 --> 00:16:02,190
Such a kid… you little kid.

181
00:16:05,990 --> 00:16:09,340
By the way, Ai.
Let me ask you something.

182
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:12,400
Feel free to ask, Gen.

183
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:18,520
So... the food you eat...

184
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:23,230
where exactly does it go?

185
00:16:24,190 --> 00:16:26,070
Well, I can't help but wonder.

186
00:16:30,510 --> 00:16:32,010
Do you want to know about me, Gen?

187
00:16:33,730 --> 00:16:36,680
In fact, my operating system
is just like a human’s in every way.

188
00:16:36,860 --> 00:16:39,600
My body doesn’t need energy from food.

189
00:16:39,630 --> 00:16:43,460
I can use solar energy or
electricity to power my body.

190
00:16:44,630 --> 00:16:49,150
The food I eat is just backup energy
that my body digests and stores.

191
00:16:49,170 --> 00:16:52,120
But if there’s too much, I can empty it.

192
00:16:52,150 --> 00:16:52,940
Empty it?

193
00:16:53,220 --> 00:16:54,120
Do you want to see?

194
00:16:54,150 --> 00:16:56,960
Um… n— no, I think I’m good.

195
00:16:57,390 --> 00:16:59,050
- I can actually show you.
- No!

196
00:17:00,190 --> 00:17:01,360
I don’t want to know anymore.

197
00:17:07,150 --> 00:17:08,010
What are you doing?

198
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:26,910
Do you truly not want to see, Gen?

199
00:17:34,440 --> 00:17:36,260
Any more than this and
I’m gonna lose my mind.

200
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:38,450
Why would you lose your mind?

201
00:17:39,230 --> 00:17:40,820
Because that’s exactly what it means.

202
00:17:42,140 --> 00:17:43,140
But why?

203
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:46,800
How long is she going to keep teasing me?!

204
00:17:54,610 --> 00:17:58,380
Hurry up and eat.
I need to wash the dishes and head out.

205
00:17:59,930 --> 00:18:00,930
Where are you going?

206
00:18:01,770 --> 00:18:03,040
It’s none of your business.

207
00:18:03,590 --> 00:18:05,000
- Let me come with you.
- No.

208
00:18:08,610 --> 00:18:10,440
Please…

209
00:18:12,230 --> 00:18:13,930
I promise to be a good girl.

210
00:18:33,900 --> 00:18:35,590
Don’t cause any trouble.

211
00:18:41,240 --> 00:18:43,590
Just eat. Come on.

212
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:16,070
What is this place?

213
00:19:20,510 --> 00:19:21,610
An art gallery.

214
00:19:22,230 --> 00:19:25,080
They often hold art exhibitions here.

215
00:19:25,440 --> 00:19:28,960
When I'm not busy or dealing with
urgent work, I like to come here and work.

216
00:19:30,150 --> 00:19:31,160
Why is that?

217
00:19:33,180 --> 00:19:34,910
Because it gives me inspiration.

218
00:19:38,880 --> 00:19:42,470
I’ve enjoyed looking at art since I was a kid.

219
00:19:43,420 --> 00:19:45,280
Whenever I look at paintings like these,

220
00:19:45,860 --> 00:19:50,010
I always find myself wondering what
was going through the artists' minds,

221
00:19:51,280 --> 00:19:53,380
what kind of emotion the colors convey,

222
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:56,020
and how heavy or light the brushstrokes feel.

223
00:19:57,950 --> 00:19:59,870
It's a shame I never got the chance to study it.

224
00:20:02,120 --> 00:20:03,120
Why is that?

225
00:20:05,130 --> 00:20:06,410
My family wouldn’t let me.

226
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:15,760
You know, I’ve always dreamed of having
my own work exhibited in an art gallery.

227
00:20:18,250 --> 00:20:22,770
Whenever I have time,
I try to take in as much as I can.

228
00:20:23,690 --> 00:20:27,070
And after coming here often,
I started bringing my work here as well.

229
00:20:28,020 --> 00:20:33,990
Before I knew it, I realized I feel
more at peace here than anywhere else.

230
00:20:35,710 --> 00:20:36,710
Strange, isn’t it?

231
00:20:40,410 --> 00:20:43,060
Now that you know,
don’t destroy anything here.

232
00:20:43,830 --> 00:20:46,030
Under no circumstances. Got it?

233
00:21:42,540 --> 00:21:44,280
Oh, you’re back.

234
00:21:46,070 --> 00:21:47,280
I don’t understand.

235
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:48,660
Understand what?

236
00:21:49,930 --> 00:21:52,730
Why do humans like overlapping strokes of color?

237
00:21:53,530 --> 00:21:58,360
I know red represents passion
and green represents calm.

238
00:21:59,290 --> 00:22:05,080
But earlier I saw a painting
called “Whisper of the Void,”

239
00:22:06,090 --> 00:22:08,980
but it was orange blending into purple.

240
00:22:10,540 --> 00:22:12,420
Layered over one another.

241
00:22:14,880 --> 00:22:16,520
Isn’t the void supposed to be black?

242
00:22:17,690 --> 00:22:18,920
I really don’t get it.

243
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:26,840
Humans are very emotionally complex beings.

244
00:22:27,450 --> 00:22:34,780
They can feel anger, pain,
despair, excitement, happiness,

245
00:22:36,450 --> 00:22:37,290
and…

246
00:22:38,970 --> 00:22:40,470
even love for someone.

247
00:22:43,970 --> 00:22:46,310
There’s no one definition
that’s completely correct.

248
00:22:47,380 --> 00:22:48,260
Well…

249
00:22:49,730 --> 00:22:52,450
One person’s pain might be black,

250
00:22:53,110 --> 00:22:56,310
while another person's void could be red.

251
00:22:57,690 --> 00:23:01,440
You’re still just a kid.
You don’t understand what emotions are yet.

252
00:23:11,190 --> 00:23:14,370
You'll understand once
you've had more life experience.

253
00:23:15,490 --> 00:23:17,990
Go play somewhere else, I need to work.

254
00:23:27,990 --> 00:23:29,340
Can you teach me?

255
00:23:31,550 --> 00:23:37,630
I want to know what anger, pain,
despair, excitement, happiness,

256
00:23:38,730 --> 00:23:40,670
or loving someone feel like.

257
00:23:42,590 --> 00:23:43,800
Can you teach me, Gen?

258
00:23:46,250 --> 00:23:47,290
Why me?

259
00:23:48,940 --> 00:23:49,910
I...

260
00:23:55,370 --> 00:23:56,990
want you to be the one to teach me.

261
00:24:20,920 --> 00:24:24,160
I...want you to be the one to teach me.

262
00:24:30,200 --> 00:24:33,370
She wants me to teach her?
What does that mean?

263
00:24:37,620 --> 00:24:39,390
Teach her what love is?

264
00:24:44,110 --> 00:24:46,960
Ugh! Ai Gen! Are you out of your mind?!

265
00:24:48,070 --> 00:24:49,010
You must be.

266
00:24:49,580 --> 00:24:50,580
I’d better sleep.

267
00:25:07,770 --> 00:25:10,190
Pull over, pull over,
pull over, pull over, pull over.

268
00:25:11,020 --> 00:25:11,940
Surprise!

269
00:25:12,580 --> 00:25:13,560
Get anything?

270
00:25:13,580 --> 00:25:16,430
Auntie, keep being nosy and
your shop’s gonna go under.

271
00:25:16,460 --> 00:25:18,610
I thought you were rushing
to the market for supplies.

272
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:22,090
Ai Josh! You damn brat,
always running your mouth at me!

273
00:25:22,390 --> 00:25:23,400
What’s the big deal?

274
00:25:23,420 --> 00:25:26,360
Stopping for ten minutes isn't going
to make me any richer or poorer.

275
00:25:28,860 --> 00:25:32,730
So, is that Barbie girl Gen’s new roommate?

276
00:25:33,940 --> 00:25:34,940
No idea, Auntie.

277
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:38,610
We came out to exercise morning and
evening, but only caught a glimpse of her.

278
00:25:39,520 --> 00:25:40,850
What do you mean morning?

279
00:25:40,870 --> 00:25:43,460
I only came in the evening.
Who did you come with this morning?

280
00:25:46,900 --> 00:25:48,670
I came out to buy fried dough sticks

281
00:25:48,690 --> 00:25:51,910
and extra-sweet soy milk with
sago pearls only for my dear wife.

282
00:25:51,930 --> 00:25:54,720
So of course I had to walk past this house.
Right, Auntie? Right?

283
00:25:54,750 --> 00:25:56,270
- Right.
- Fine then.

284
00:25:56,460 --> 00:25:57,880
Good thing you got the order right.

285
00:25:58,580 --> 00:25:59,230
Hey.

286
00:26:00,240 --> 00:26:01,250
There she is!

287
00:26:01,710 --> 00:26:03,340
Ai Josh, let’s hide the bike.

288
00:26:04,570 --> 00:26:07,600
- You want Gen to come and tear me apart?!
- If you cooked as fast as you snoop around,

289
00:26:07,620 --> 00:26:09,300
you’d be a billionaire by now.

290
00:26:26,500 --> 00:26:27,740
What on earth are you doing?

291
00:26:31,360 --> 00:26:33,320
Gen, help me.

292
00:26:35,390 --> 00:26:39,140
How does someone manage to turn
simple plant watering into such a disaster?

293
00:26:42,920 --> 00:26:44,410
Come on, I’ll help you.

294
00:26:47,640 --> 00:26:49,000
Ai! Stop spraying!

295
00:26:49,100 --> 00:26:50,730
I told you to stop, Ai!

296
00:27:18,140 --> 00:27:19,050
So soft...

297
00:27:19,900 --> 00:27:21,040
It feels so real.

298
00:27:56,270 --> 00:27:59,040
Why do humans use their
body parts to touch each other?

299
00:28:01,730 --> 00:28:05,500
Based on my data, humans engage
in physical interaction through touch,

300
00:28:05,780 --> 00:28:07,910
including the exchange of
fluids via mucous membranes.

301
00:28:08,150 --> 00:28:11,420
Such as in the oral cavity
like earlier, and there’s also—

302
00:28:13,930 --> 00:28:18,170
You call what just happened
an “exchange of oral fluids”?

303
00:28:21,360 --> 00:28:22,360
Is it not?

304
00:28:27,830 --> 00:28:28,880
Why are you laughing?

305
00:28:39,280 --> 00:28:40,770
It’s called a kiss.

306
00:28:51,680 --> 00:28:53,170
It’s called a kiss.

307
00:29:01,670 --> 00:29:03,510
They’re definitely partners, Auntie!

308
00:29:04,020 --> 00:29:05,290
Could they be talking partners?

309
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:08,720
Ooh, talking lip to lip, huh?

310
00:29:09,360 --> 00:29:11,990
What else do you expect them to
speak with if not their lips? Pu—

311
00:29:12,020 --> 00:29:13,300
You’re filthy-mouthed.

312
00:29:14,300 --> 00:29:18,620
I was gonna say pupil, pulse, and so on, Auntie.
Gosh, your mind is in the gutter.

313
00:29:18,650 --> 00:29:20,110
Just shut the hell up.

314
00:29:22,050 --> 00:29:23,730
Why can’t I see anything?

315
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:30,690
Hey, get up and go get changed.

316
00:29:31,940 --> 00:29:33,470
Or you want another fluid exchange?

317
00:29:52,500 --> 00:29:55,470
They’re totally a couple.
P’Ai’s face is bright red.

318
00:29:59,930 --> 00:30:01,720
- We must spread this around.
- Yes, Auntie.

319
00:30:01,740 --> 00:30:02,800
Where should we start?

320
00:30:02,830 --> 00:30:04,250
How about my restaurant?

321
00:30:05,920 --> 00:30:07,800
Guess we’re not going
to the market anymore.

322
00:30:07,830 --> 00:30:09,330
I’m heading home to game.

323
00:30:24,840 --> 00:30:27,380
Why haven't you changed yet?
You're going to get sick.

324
00:30:29,010 --> 00:30:30,380
I’m a robot.

325
00:30:31,470 --> 00:30:35,600
That’s true, but even if you don't get
sick, you got water all over my house.

326
00:30:35,840 --> 00:30:37,470
Come on, go get changed.
Let's go.

327
00:30:40,330 --> 00:30:41,330
What’s wrong?

328
00:30:43,390 --> 00:30:44,440
I don’t know.

329
00:30:45,150 --> 00:30:47,860
I feel strange when Master—

330
00:30:50,250 --> 00:30:53,060
I feel strange when you touch me, Gen.

331
00:30:53,090 --> 00:30:54,530
My systems are under excessive load.

332
00:30:54,560 --> 00:30:56,790
Increased motor speed
has elevated my temperature.

333
00:30:57,010 --> 00:30:58,280
I need to cool my systems down.

334
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:10,260
Look, I have no idea what you’re talking about.
And stop backing away from me.

335
00:31:10,280 --> 00:31:11,780
Now I’m soaked all over again.

336
00:31:11,800 --> 00:31:13,260
Then let me go, Gen.

337
00:31:13,490 --> 00:31:16,590
No way. If I let you go, you’re
just going to get the floor all wet.

338
00:31:16,610 --> 00:31:18,620
- I'll wipe it up.
- I don't believe you.

339
00:31:20,090 --> 00:31:21,620
Just stay still, Ai—

340
00:31:22,010 --> 00:31:22,760
Ah!

341
00:31:23,590 --> 00:31:26,500
I'm sorry!
Did I do something wrong?

342
00:31:28,080 --> 00:31:31,820
I should be the one asking you that.
Did I upset you, Gen?

343
00:31:32,740 --> 00:31:34,260
Are you going to chase me away again?

344
00:31:36,150 --> 00:31:39,140
Why do you have to go
as far as shutting me down?

345
00:31:39,750 --> 00:31:42,340
Do you hate me, Gen?
Do you dislike me?

346
00:31:47,450 --> 00:31:51,140
I don’t hate you.
And I’m not upset with you either.

347
00:31:53,220 --> 00:31:55,140
But you were trying to shut me down.

348
00:31:55,540 --> 00:31:56,990
I wasn't trying to shut you down.

349
00:31:57,410 --> 00:32:00,240
I don’t even know where your power switch is.

350
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:04,570
You didn’t come with an instruction
manual when you showed up.

351
00:32:09,420 --> 00:32:11,320
- Is that true?
- Yes.

352
00:32:13,090 --> 00:32:14,100
I don’t believe you.

353
00:32:14,340 --> 00:32:15,130
What?

354
00:32:15,610 --> 00:32:17,900
You tried to send me back to the company before.

355
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,250
What is it?

356
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:36,340
I promise I won't chase you away anymore.

357
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:37,980
And I won't shut you down either.

358
00:32:43,710 --> 00:32:47,340
What does that have to do
with extending your pinky finger?

359
00:32:50,470 --> 00:32:53,700
One moment, please. I need some
time to search for more information.

360
00:33:01,470 --> 00:33:05,300
A pinky promise is when two
people make a promise to each other.

361
00:33:06,900 --> 00:33:10,780
And I promise I will never
do anything that harms you.

362
00:33:11,600 --> 00:33:12,390
Okay?

363
00:33:14,440 --> 00:33:15,340
Trust me.

364
00:33:17,370 --> 00:33:18,140
Please?

365
00:33:24,490 --> 00:33:29,260
And just like that… a promise
between me and a robot began.

366
00:34:21,639 --> 00:34:22,409
Strange.

367
00:34:43,050 --> 00:34:44,290
I'm feeling it again.

368
00:35:20,070 --> 00:35:21,080
What’s the matter?

369
00:35:21,420 --> 00:35:22,430
I don’t know.

370
00:35:22,750 --> 00:35:25,990
I woke up with a sore shoulder.
Like something was pressing on it all night.

371
00:35:31,770 --> 00:35:33,860
Why did you suddenly want
to come to the art gallery?

372
00:35:36,180 --> 00:35:37,400
I want to understand.

373
00:35:37,920 --> 00:35:38,780
Understand what?

374
00:35:40,360 --> 00:35:41,230
You.

375
00:35:46,740 --> 00:35:48,550
You want to understand human emotions, right?

376
00:35:49,070 --> 00:35:52,350
Do I need to teach you that
your words can cause misunderstandings?

377
00:35:54,500 --> 00:35:57,910
Just go look at whatever you want.
I’ll be working at my usual spot.

378
00:36:00,230 --> 00:36:02,230
And don’t wander off too far.

379
00:36:02,390 --> 00:36:04,160
Think carefully before responding to anyone.

380
00:36:04,190 --> 00:36:06,290
You don’t want to end up
getting taken apart, do you?

381
00:36:19,250 --> 00:36:21,010
Why the hell are you flustered, Ai Gen?

382
00:36:21,680 --> 00:36:23,520
She just wants to understand humans.

383
00:36:23,920 --> 00:36:26,910
She wants to understand you
because you’re a human.

384
00:36:27,140 --> 00:36:29,320
Did you forget how to
connect ideas like in exams?

385
00:36:29,340 --> 00:36:31,760
That’s all there is to it.
Don’t overthink it.

386
00:36:31,780 --> 00:36:34,210
Don't flatter yourself. Stop it.

387
00:36:36,180 --> 00:36:38,800
Why is your heart racing over
a robot that isn’t even a month old?

388
00:36:45,200 --> 00:36:46,020
Sorry!

389
00:36:52,450 --> 00:36:53,240
Kaew…

390
00:36:55,150 --> 00:36:56,590
So this is how it’s going to be, Gen?

391
00:36:57,110 --> 00:36:58,380
I’ve made my decision, Kaew.

392
00:36:58,840 --> 00:36:59,980
Don’t be crazy.

393
00:37:00,430 --> 00:37:02,450
You’re one step away from a promotion.

394
00:37:03,060 --> 00:37:04,760
But you’re just going to throw it all away

395
00:37:04,790 --> 00:37:07,470
because you suddenly had an epiphany
that you want to draw?!

396
00:37:07,830 --> 00:37:11,870
What about everything you’ve built up?
Years of experience? Work history?

397
00:37:13,160 --> 00:37:15,050
Do you know how much money you’re making here?

398
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:18,440
And what about the stability you always wanted?

399
00:37:19,830 --> 00:37:22,000
Didn’t you say you wanted
to make your mother proud?

400
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:26,840
So you’re just going to throw it
all away for some foolish dream?!

401
00:37:26,870 --> 00:37:28,860
It’s not a foolish dream, Kaew.

402
00:37:33,350 --> 00:37:34,350
What about me?

403
00:37:36,190 --> 00:37:37,560
Everything’s still the same.

404
00:37:38,760 --> 00:37:39,520
No.

405
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:41,560
It will never be the same.

406
00:37:42,770 --> 00:37:44,940
If you choose that dream over me…

407
00:37:47,140 --> 00:37:48,260
then we’re through.

408
00:37:48,280 --> 00:37:49,750
Kaew, please don't do this.

409
00:37:50,070 --> 00:37:52,690
No, you’re the one making the choice here.

410
00:37:54,550 --> 00:37:55,410
So choose.

411
00:37:57,430 --> 00:37:58,510
Are you staying or leaving?

412
00:38:13,410 --> 00:38:16,090
Gen! Come back here right now! Gen!

413
00:38:16,950 --> 00:38:18,440
Gen! Gen!!

414
00:38:23,100 --> 00:38:23,890
Gen.

415
00:38:28,830 --> 00:38:30,060
You still keep it?

416
00:38:38,310 --> 00:38:39,610
It’s been a long time.

417
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:42,240
Mm, it’s been a long time.

418
00:38:44,500 --> 00:38:47,720
Since… you left to chase your dream.

419
00:38:49,370 --> 00:38:50,380
And…

420
00:38:53,080 --> 00:38:54,540
it looks like you’re still dreaming.

421
00:38:56,980 --> 00:39:00,890
I... just remembered I’ve got
something to do. Excuse me.

422
00:39:01,160 --> 00:39:02,260
Wait, Gen!

423
00:39:03,250 --> 00:39:05,910
What's the rush?
We haven’t seen each other in so long.

424
00:39:06,910 --> 00:39:07,680
Gen.

425
00:39:09,370 --> 00:39:12,120
Can we just let bygones be bygones?

426
00:39:16,740 --> 00:39:20,710
Well… I know we didn’t end things on good terms.

427
00:39:22,220 --> 00:39:24,000
But that was ages ago.

428
00:39:26,180 --> 00:39:28,010
Are you going to avoid me forever?

429
00:39:32,160 --> 00:39:35,890
At least… for the sake of our good memories.

430
00:39:38,430 --> 00:39:41,360
I... don't want to lose you as a friend.

431
00:39:48,870 --> 00:39:51,730
At least, if you still consider me one.

432
00:39:57,040 --> 00:39:57,750
Mm.

433
00:39:59,210 --> 00:40:01,150
That’s wonderful. What a relief.

434
00:40:01,870 --> 00:40:03,800
By the way, next week,

435
00:40:04,340 --> 00:40:06,830
I’m meeting up with the friends
we joined the company with.

436
00:40:06,850 --> 00:40:07,780
Remember them?

437
00:40:09,510 --> 00:40:11,690
Kate's working in the States now,

438
00:40:12,510 --> 00:40:14,100
but she'll be back next week.

439
00:40:14,850 --> 00:40:16,230
You should come see everyone.

440
00:40:17,420 --> 00:40:19,260
They all want to meet you.

441
00:40:21,610 --> 00:40:24,720
I... I have to go.

442
00:40:27,560 --> 00:40:29,970
Then… call me if you change your mind.

443
00:40:30,980 --> 00:40:32,130
My number's still the same.

444
00:40:33,970 --> 00:40:35,550
You still remember it, right?

445
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:55,590
I'm glad you still keep that bracelet.

446
00:41:10,040 --> 00:41:11,300
Guess who?

447
00:41:14,630 --> 00:41:15,650
That’s tough.

448
00:41:16,010 --> 00:41:18,060
Come on, give it a try.

449
00:41:18,490 --> 00:41:21,760
Could it be the apple of someone’s eye?

450
00:41:21,780 --> 00:41:23,490
Whose? Answer quickly!

451
00:41:24,290 --> 00:41:26,350
Well... mine, of course.

452
00:41:29,120 --> 00:41:34,850
And the apple of someone’s eye
has a gift for you!

453
00:41:35,820 --> 00:41:36,800
What is it?

454
00:41:37,490 --> 00:41:38,250
Open it.

455
00:41:41,120 --> 00:41:41,820
Oh.

456
00:41:44,260 --> 00:41:45,120
Wow.

457
00:41:47,910 --> 00:41:49,450
A gift for passing the project.

458
00:41:51,500 --> 00:41:55,580
It might not be expensive,
but it’s from the heart.

459
00:41:56,970 --> 00:41:57,900
You like it?

460
00:41:59,050 --> 00:41:59,840
It’s cute.

461
00:42:01,110 --> 00:42:02,030
Thank you.

462
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:15,780
I liked it.

463
00:42:16,910 --> 00:42:17,760
I did.

464
00:42:18,790 --> 00:42:20,030
And I still do.

465
00:42:25,540 --> 00:42:27,050
Do you like bracelets, Gen?

466
00:42:33,140 --> 00:42:34,150
I...

467
00:42:39,620 --> 00:42:41,010
I’m not sure either.

468
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:44,040
Why is that?

469
00:42:46,640 --> 00:42:48,300
Because I thought I could do it.

470
00:42:50,660 --> 00:42:52,700
Follow my dream in a way
everyone would accept.

471
00:42:53,660 --> 00:42:55,650
And then tell the one who gave me this bracelet,

472
00:42:57,430 --> 00:42:58,470
“I did it.”

473
00:42:59,560 --> 00:43:00,410
“See?”

474
00:43:01,190 --> 00:43:02,610
“You can be proud of me now.”

475
00:43:03,710 --> 00:43:05,210
“Can I have another chance?”

476
00:43:10,490 --> 00:43:12,020
But in the end, it was just a dream.

477
00:43:15,890 --> 00:43:17,370
You’ve got some nerve, Gen.

478
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:22,760
Right now, you’re still just a freelancer
who takes on any job anyone pays you for.

479
00:43:23,300 --> 00:43:26,050
And you really think you can just
go back and ask for another chance?

480
00:43:31,000 --> 00:43:35,390
So if I gave you a bracelet,
would you like me?

481
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:39,130
Why?

482
00:43:39,610 --> 00:43:43,040
I want you to like me.
Do I need a reason for that?

483
00:43:50,910 --> 00:43:54,150
What... should I do?

484
00:43:57,880 --> 00:43:59,730
Do what you want.

485
00:44:02,800 --> 00:44:06,410
You said humans have emotions and desires.

486
00:44:07,150 --> 00:44:10,360
I believe everything you do is good.

487
00:44:15,760 --> 00:44:17,690
Aren't you placing a bit too much faith in me?

488
00:44:18,110 --> 00:44:19,790
You’re the one who taught me.

489
00:44:38,930 --> 00:44:41,100
I like it when you touch me like this.

490
00:44:55,850 --> 00:44:59,490
Have I become so desperate that I’m
getting advice from a three-week-old robot?

491
00:45:04,400 --> 00:45:05,560
Where are you going, Gen?

492
00:45:07,920 --> 00:45:09,250
I'm going to set things straight.

493
00:45:10,410 --> 00:45:11,340
Thanks.

494
00:45:36,090 --> 00:45:40,060
Seriously, the picanha at JR is to die for.

495
00:45:40,090 --> 00:45:41,730
I'm craving it so much.

496
00:45:41,750 --> 00:45:44,560
And the truffle spaghetti is really good too.

497
00:45:44,890 --> 00:45:47,550
Hello there, gorgeous!

498
00:45:49,380 --> 00:45:50,630
Look who’s finally here.

499
00:45:56,280 --> 00:45:58,720
Gen: "Be there in 10 minutes."

500
00:46:00,190 --> 00:46:05,580
Is it just me, or did someone go
totally all-out with her outfit tonight?

501
00:46:07,280 --> 00:46:08,520
Maybe a little.

502
00:46:09,060 --> 00:46:11,430
Hey, do you really think she’ll show up?

503
00:46:12,730 --> 00:46:14,660
She’s been out of the picture for years.

504
00:46:15,020 --> 00:46:17,280
I wouldn’t have the guts to come if I were her.

505
00:46:18,470 --> 00:46:23,750
Because she talked big, saying
she was going to go chase her dreams.

506
00:46:24,040 --> 00:46:25,470
Heh. And look what happened.

507
00:46:25,490 --> 00:46:29,570
The rising star everyone expected
to start her own company someday

508
00:46:29,890 --> 00:46:32,170
and become some hotshot CEO...

509
00:46:32,200 --> 00:46:35,320
what's the phrase for her situation now?

510
00:46:35,350 --> 00:46:36,710
Living hand to mouth?

511
00:46:38,260 --> 00:46:39,790
Hey, don't laugh.

512
00:46:40,830 --> 00:46:44,790
I know you only went after her
because she was talented.

513
00:46:44,820 --> 00:46:48,100
Come on, that’s ancient history.
Let’s not talk about it.

514
00:46:48,850 --> 00:46:49,850
Don’t lie.

515
00:46:50,100 --> 00:46:51,710
If it were really ancient history,

516
00:46:51,730 --> 00:46:54,050
you wouldn’t have dragged us here
to rub it in Gen’s face.

517
00:46:54,300 --> 00:46:55,310
Am I right?

518
00:46:56,600 --> 00:46:58,370
Just tell us what you want us to do.

519
00:46:58,770 --> 00:47:00,930
Guys, don't be like this.

520
00:47:01,370 --> 00:47:03,300
Aren't we just meeting up for a dinner?

521
00:47:03,590 --> 00:47:04,440
No.

522
00:47:05,360 --> 00:47:10,320
She needs to be shown what happens
when you make the wrong choice.

523
00:47:13,860 --> 00:47:16,420
But you were the one who dumped Gen.

524
00:47:16,740 --> 00:47:20,640
You said that she came crying
and begging for you to take her back.

525
00:47:20,950 --> 00:47:23,460
Since you don't care about
her anymore, just let it go.

526
00:47:23,750 --> 00:47:24,790
Amen.

527
00:47:26,880 --> 00:47:29,290
Hope you never lose that saintly act of yours.

528
00:47:29,590 --> 00:47:30,410
So.

529
00:47:31,330 --> 00:47:33,280
Should we just walk all over her tonight?

530
00:47:34,850 --> 00:47:35,860
Obviously.

531
00:47:36,540 --> 00:47:39,960
Who’d want to be with someone
who has nothing going for them?

532
00:47:40,570 --> 00:47:42,040
How dare she dumped someone like me.

533
00:47:43,290 --> 00:47:44,460
That’s the spirit.

534
00:47:44,780 --> 00:47:48,400
Let’s humiliate her so badly she has to
hide under a skirt and never come out.

535
00:47:49,260 --> 00:47:51,490
- How about my skirt? It’s pretty long.
- That’ll do.

536
00:48:47,240 --> 00:48:49,680
Hey. Who is that?
She’s so beautiful.

537
00:49:17,430 --> 00:49:18,280
Ai?

538
00:49:35,480 --> 00:49:36,480
Sawasdee ka.

539
00:50:16,370 --> 00:50:17,740
Ai!!!

540
00:50:18,670 --> 00:50:19,890
Yes?

541
00:50:21,000 --> 00:50:22,900
Exactly how much stuff did you order?!

542
00:50:23,990 --> 00:50:25,650
I ordered them so you would like me, Gen.

543
00:50:26,470 --> 00:50:27,380
Like this.

544
00:50:28,200 --> 00:50:31,360
Which style do you prefer?
I got them in every style.

545
00:50:36,400 --> 00:50:38,080
Do you like it, Master?

546
00:50:40,820 --> 00:50:41,890
Ai! You—!

547
00:50:43,630 --> 00:50:44,980
Throw everything away!!!

548
00:50:47,830 --> 00:50:50,830
English Subtitles by Saowalak K.

